parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt Failure - Door-Mounted Seat Belts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of door-mounted seat belts can cause occupants to be ejected from the vehicle or not be properly restrained in the event of an accident, leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Seat belts are attached to the door instead of the body
seat belts stick or are difficult to open
seat belts do not tighten properly
seat belts break or fail during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not properly restrain the occupant, leading to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belt retractor fails to lock
seat belt retractor fails to tighten
seat belt retractor makes a snapping or clicking noise
seat belt retractor has been replaced multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt anchor can cause the seat belt to not properly restrain the occupant, leading to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belt anchor deteriorates due to heat and sun fatigue
seat belt anchor fails to hold the seat belt in place.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate seat belt restraint can cause occupants to be injured or ejected from the vehicle in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belt does not tighten properly
seat belt allows the occupant to move more than an inch
seat belt does not lock upon impact.
